<span class="user-postname"><span>Garry</span></span><span class="user-date"> on November 15, 2007 02:19 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>Note to readers who&#8217;ve come back for more&#8212;</p>


	<p>I&#8217;ve made updates tonight since my original post.  I included a small patch as a part of the regular setup.  It helps gitosis find git if you have git installed in a non-standard location (let subprocesses see your modified <span class="caps">PATH</span>).  Also, it fixes a <span class="caps">BIG</span> show stopper git-checkout-index error if you run git 1.5.3 and higher (which I highly recommend) on your server.  No issue was seen with git 1.5.2.x and lower.</p>


	<p>Thanks to Tv and spearce in #git for the help.</p>
</div>
