<!-- comments layout -->
<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><span>Garry</span></span><span class="user-date"> on November 20, 2007 02:27 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>grempe</p>


	<p>git-daemon does not necessarily integrate with gitosis, it just runs along side gitosisnand allows read-only public access to the repos you choose.  that said, changes to gitosis since the time of writing this tutorial have made progress in allowing you to control git-daemon and gitweb settings from gitosis.  That&#8217;s very cool, and you&#8217;ll see examples of how to do that in example.conf.  As for projects.list, i&#8217;m not sure what that does.</p>


	<p>To use basic auth on some repos, i think you need to edit the lighttpd.conf for gitweb, there&#8217;s not a way to do that directly in gitosis</p>
</div>
<div class="add-comment-line"><!-- add line here --></div>
