<!-- comments layout -->
<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><span>Garry</span></span><span class="user-date"> on February 12, 2008 02:10 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>ChrisB, the &#8220;system&#8221; aspect of the adduser command makes the user in a certain <span class="caps">UID</span> range and group of &#8220;nogroup&#8221;.  According to the man page, it also makes it so &#8220;logins [are] disabled&#8221;.</p>


	<p>The Ubuntu 6.06 man page also states that logins are disabled, however I had no problems with the git user being a &#8220;system&#8221; user.  I haven&#8217;t tried installing gitosis on 7.10 yet.</p>


	<p>So I&#8217;d say leave off&#8212;system to adduser if it&#8217;s not working for ya.</p>
</div>
<div class="add-comment-line"><!-- add line here --></div>
</div>

<!-- comments layout -->
<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><span>mtkd</span></span><span class="user-date"> on March 20, 2008 11:58 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>I had issues getting this to work on a vanilla Ubuntu server install.</p>


	<p>When I did &#8220;git clone git@ULAMP1:gitosis-admin.git&#8221; from the client, it prompted for a password then gave a Permission Denied.</p>


	<p>When I checked /var/log/auth.log:</p>


	<p>User git from xxxx not allowed because not listed in AllowUsers</p>


	<p>I added the users to AllowUsers but still had the issue, doubled checked everything, it turned out I needed to add the user to a Group and then the Group to AllowGroups (I used Webmin to add the user to the group and restart <span class="caps">SSH</span>).</p>
</div>
