<span class="user-postname"><span>leed25d</span></span><span class="user-date"> on April 12, 2008 11:32 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>,<del>&#8212;</del>
| id_rsa.pub above is your public <span class="caps">SSH</span> key that you copied to the
| server. I recommend you put it in /tmp so the git user won&#8217;t have
| permission problems when trying to read it. Success looks like:
`<del>&#8212;</del></p>


	<p>I believe that this is a somewhat bad idea.  Some systems can be, and
frequently are, configured to clear the contents of /tmp at boot time.</p>
