<span class="user-postname"><span>pzingg</span></span><span class="user-date"> on April 14, 2008 10:48 PM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>On my setup (git server is <span class="caps">OS X 10</span>.5 Server, with git-core installed via macports and gitosis installed using <span class="caps">OS X</span>&#8217;s python 2.5; git client is <span class="caps">OS X 10</span>.4), I had to edit the .ssh/authorized_keys file to use a path:</p>


	<p>command=&#8221;/usr/local/bin/gitosis-serve user@host&#8221;, ...</p>


	<p>Otherwise I would get this when trying to do the remote git clone:</p>


	<p>bash: gitosis-serve: command not found
fatal: The remote end hung up unexpectedly
fetch-pack from &#8216;git@gitserver.example.com:gitosis-admin.git&#8217; failed.</p>


	<p>I also put the path to the macports area (/opt/local/bin) into the .bashrc in the git server&#8217;s git user&#8217;s home directory, so that the git-xxx commands would be found.</p>
