<!-- comments layout -->
<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><span>DAparo</span></span><span class="user-date"> on July 03, 2008 09:00 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>@DrMark</p>


	<p>Sorry for the long delay in getting back to you.</p>


	<p>I think it may be repository permissions too.
     This is what got me.  You run script/server w/a user that has a public cert in the gitosis repos, but the apache/passenger user doesn&#8217;t.  Simple solution&#8230;  create a cert for your passenger user. Add it to gitosis server and assign permissions in gitosis.conf.
     I gave my apache user read permissions on the entire direstory and all files / folders within.  I didn&#8217;t do anything special with the any .git configs. 
     I did have to run &#8220;ruby script/runner &#8220;Repository.fetch_changesets&#8221; -e production&#8221; first.</p>


	<p>Hope this helps&#8230;</p>
</div>
<div class="add-comment-line"><!-- add line here --></div>
