<span class="user-postname"><span>Pegolon</span></span><span class="user-date"> on July 24, 2008 01:25 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>Hi,
to install gitosis on a Mac <span class="caps">OS X</span> Leopard Server I used the recent version of Python 2.5.2 of MacPorts and the hashlib:
&gt; port install python25 py25-hashlib
which will be installed into /opt/local/bin, so make sure it is included <span class="caps">PATH</span> before /usr/bin where the original version is.</p>


	<p>To install the setup tools:
&gt; cd /usr/src
&gt; wget http://peak.telecommunity.com/dist/ez_setup.py
&gt; python ez_setup.py</p>


	<p>Source: http://peak.telecommunity.com/DevCenter/EasyInstall#installation-instructions</p>


	<p>Then &#8220;python /usr/src/setup.py install&#8221; will work as described above.</p>


	<p>Cheers,
Markus</p>
</div>
