<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><a href="http://www.michael-noll.com/">Michael G. Noll</a></span><span class="user-date"> on August 01, 2008 06:08 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>Thanks for this tutorial, garry!</p>


	<p>Since you haven&#8217;t mentioned it in this tutorial (I also haven&#8217;t found it in the gitosis documentation), you might want to add that a user can also have multiple <span class="caps">SSH</span> keys for authentication, e.g. one public key from work and one public key from home.</p>


	<p>Just add the respective public keys to &#8220;keydir/&lt;user&gt;.pub&#8221;, i.e. one key per line in the file. For instance, if user &#8220;jsmith&#8221; uses three different <span class="caps">SSH</span> keys to connect via gitosis to a shared git repository, he would have three keys (= three lines)  in &#8220;keydir/jsmith.pub&#8221;.</p>


	<p>Hope this helps,
Michael</p>
</div>
<div class="add-comment-line"><!-- add line here --></div>
</div>

