<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><a href="http://www.asinglepixel.com">Graham Perks</a></span><span class="user-date"> on August 05, 2008 08:33 PM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>If you this this error when you go to access the remote repository:</p>


	<p>bash: gitosis-serve: command not found</p>


	<p>Then edit the remote &#8220;git&#8221; user&#8217;s .bashrc and include these lines to ensure /usr/local/bin is in the path.</p>


	<p>echo $PATH | grep -q -s &#8221;/usr/local/bin&#8221; 
if [ $? -eq 1 ] ; then
    <span class="caps">PATH</span>=/usr/local/bin:/usr/local/sbin:$PATH
    export <span class="caps">PATH</span>
fi</p>


	<p>A prior poster&#8217;s comment about manually editing authorized_keys is a poor workaround, since gitosis will rewrite that file when you add/remove users.</p>
</div>
<div class="add-comment-line"><!-- add line here --></div>
</div>

<!-- comments layout -->
<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><a href="http://www.asinglepixel.com">Graham Perks</a></span><span class="user-date"> on August 05, 2008 08:35 PM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>That little bit of .bashrc goodness should be:</p>


	<p>echo $PATH | grep -q -s &#8221;/usr/local/bin&#8221;</p>


	<p>if [ $? -eq 1 ] ; then</p>


	<pre><code>PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/local/sbin:$PATH</code></pre>


	<pre><code>export PATH</code></pre>


	<p>fi</p>
</div>
