<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><a href="http://gigism.blogspot.com">lenards</a></span><span class="user-date"> on August 23, 2008 05:30 PM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>If you&#8217;re getting <span class="caps">ERROR</span>:gitosis.serve.main:Repository read access denied</p>


	<p>you&#8217;ll want to verify that you&#8217;re keys are correct &#8211; check the local versus the .pub file in ~/repositories/gitosis-admin/gitosis-export/</p>


	<p>then &#8211; make sure that you follow the tutorial&#8230; I was getting this message when I had not added my repo to the gitosis.conf prior to pushing up the repo&#8230; so make sure that you have the group and such in your gitosis.conf prior to doing your `git push origin master`</p>


	<p>I spent a ton of time searching about getting this going &#8230;</p>


	<p>if you&#8217;re getting the os.py error &#8211; check and see if `git-shell` is in the install directory&#8230; /usr/bin or /usr/local/bin &#8230; I needed to do a symlink to `git-shell` from my install directory&#8230; I have git in /opt/git-1.6.0 with a symlink to that as /opt/git &#8230; so as I update git &#8211; I just relink and that&#8217;ll get the `git-shell` updated too.</p>


	<p>Hope this saves some time for people</p>
</div>
<div class="add-comment-line"><!-- add line here --></div>
</div>

