<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><span>Garry</span></span><span class="user-date"> on September 11, 2008 04:48 PM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>@lobo_tuerto, if you&#8217;ve followed the directions here, you&#8217;ll want to look at this file:</p>


	<pre><code>/home/git/.ssh/authorized_keys</code></pre>


	<p>Put in your new public key in there, being careful to preserve the &#8220;command=...&#8221; stuff.</p>


	<p>Then update your gitosis-admin repo with your new pub key.  Push this.  You should be allowed to push now b/c you changed authorized_keys.  Gitosis will overwrite authorized_keys at this point, but it is OK b/c you put your new pub key into gitosis-admin repo.</p>


	<p>That should do it.  I&#8217;m typing this from memory, so hopefully I got it right. ;)</p>
</div>
<div class="add-comment-line"><!-- add line here --></div>
