<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><span>MikkelFJ</span></span><span class="user-date"> on September 24, 2008 05:14 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>This does not work on Debian Etch with ssh password login disabled.
workaround: add password to git user.
reason: debian locks passwordless accounts
insecure workaround 2: UsePAM = yes in sshd_config &#8211; but you shouldn&#8217;t have <span class="caps">PAM</span> login active.</p>


	<p>Excellent article
worked out of the box the first time I tried (except installation see below).</p>


	<p>But then I secured my system according to:
http://articles.slicehost.com/2007/9/5/debian-etch-setup-page-1</p>


	<p>/etc/ssh/sshd_config:
  UsePAM = no</p>


	<p>If UsePAM is set to yes, it will work even with password authentication disabled, but it is not fully secure.
With UsePAM set to no, it will only work if a password is added to the git(osis) user account.</p>


	<p>The reason is that Debian locks passwordless accounts, but somehow pam_unix circumvents this over ssh hence it will work with UsePAM = yes.</p>


	<p>Debian Etch install procedure:</p>


	<p>$ apt-get install python-setuptools &#38;&#38; apt-get install gitosis
$ sudo passwd gitosis
$ &lt;prompt password for&gt;</p>


	<p>Dependencies on python-setuptools does not work correctly (at least in my version) so it must be installed first as the article also says.
If gitosis is attempted installed first, it must be removed before python tools is installed_</p>


	<p>$ apt-get remove gitosis</p>


	<p>If gitosis-init is called again with a new public key, the old key will remain installed.
Remove content of .ssh and repositories directories in the git user account , then run gitosis-init again.</p>


	<p>Debian installer creates user &#8220;gitosis&#8221; with home directory &#8221;/srv/gitosis&#8221; which is fine, but different from the above article. It is also possible to manually create a &#8220;git&#8221; user according to the above.
In both cases a password must be added on secured systems.</p>


	<p>Apparently the update hook has the correct permissions from install, so this isn&#8217;t necessary to change.</p>


	<p>gitosis is a very nice tool</p>


	<p>Mikkel</p>
</div>
<div class="add-comment-line"><!-- add line here --></div>
</div>

