<!-- comments layout -->
<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><span>Garry</span></span><span class="user-date"> on November 20, 2008 01:17 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>Peter, if your /etc/ssh/sshd_config file has &#8220;UsePAM yes&#8221;, then <span class="caps">PAM</span> may have denied you logging in as your &#8220;git&#8221; user because of various reasons.  The most common one I&#8217;ve seen is that the account is &#8220;locked&#8221;.  What makes an account locked is dependent on your <span class="caps">PAM</span> setup.  Changing the password field for the &#8220;git&#8221; user in /etc/shadow from ! to a * has been reported to solve the problem.</p>
</div>
<div class="add-comment-line"><!-- add line here --></div>
</div>

