anyway the basic workflow to git-svn for an existing repository is
Don&#8217;t run git svn init bc you&#8217;ll create a new repo, just add this to your .git/config file:
[svn-remote &#8220;svn&#8221;]
        url = https://svn.richapplabs.com/tech/modcart-dev/trunk/ModCloth
        fetch = :refs/remotes/git-svn
then run
git fetch 
if you want to have only part of the history run:
git fecth -r &lt;revision_number&gt;</p>


