<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><a href="http://evalinux.wordpress.com">Tzury Bar Yochay</a></span><span class="user-date"> on December 14, 2008 07:07 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>As far as I managed to gather from the <span class="caps">README</span> file here is the magic:
the linux user (ssh/login) is a single user which created without password.
This user is shared amongst al the repositories you are hosting.</p>


	<p>Since all keys at ~/.ssh/authorized_keys are defined with command=&#8217;gitosis-serve&#8217; option, all the commands are to be enforced to go via gitosis-serve which apply a filter on the commands supplied and act accordingly.</p>


	<p>you can read more about this command option at: http://www.eng.cam.ac.uk/help/jpmg/ssh/authorized_keys_howto.html</p>


	<p>hoped I helped yo uand other who will visit this page  in the future .</p>
</div>
