<p>@Wouter</p>


	<p>As far as I managed to gather from the <span class="caps">README</span> file here is the magic: the linux user (ssh/login) is a single user which created without password. This user is shared amongst al the repositories you are hosting.</p>


	<p>Since all keys at ~/.ssh/authorized_keys are defined with command=gitosis-serve option, all the commands are to be enforced to go via gitosis-serve which apply a filter on the commands supplied and act accordingly.</p>


	<p>you can read more about this command option at: http://www.eng.cam.ac.uk/help/jpmg/ssh/authorized_keys_howto.html</p>


