<span class="user-postname"><span>Andrew Uselton</span></span><span class="user-date"> on February 07, 2009 02:24 PM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>I found that the setuptools <span class="caps">RPM</span> did not install correctly.  The manual steps that follow worked.  This is essentially what &#8220;sudo rpm -ivh &#8230;&#8221; should have done:</p>


	<p>cd ~/src
rpm2cpio ~/download/setuptools-0.6c9-1.src.rpm | cpio -ivd
tar xvfz setuptools-0.6c9.tar.gz
cd setuptools-0.6c9
sudo python setup.py install</p>
</div>
