<span class="user-postname"><span>Arlen Cuss</span></span><span class="user-date"> on March 25, 2009 02:59 PM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>As it turns out, it&#8217;s important that a valid <strong>running</strong> shell is suggested.</p>


	<p>I tried using /bin/false to prevent log-in (though it turns out ~git/.ssh/authorized_keys does more than a good enough job of this), and it resulted in me getting no debug messages, nothin&#8217;! Just &#8220;The remote end hung up unexpectedly&#8221;.</p>


	<p>So go ahead and use /bin/sh, they can&#8217;t use it anyway.</p>
</div>
