<!-- comments layout -->
<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><span>dajoe13</span></span><span class="user-date"> on April 04, 2009 09:14 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>re: bash: gitosis-serve: command not found</p>


	<p>I solved this problem.  The path set by sshd before running the command in the authorized_key file is /usr/sbin:/sbin:/usr/bin:/bin, at least on my <span class="caps">SUSE 11</span>.1 system.  I believe this is based on <span class="caps">PATH</span> set on ssh at compile time.  The .bashrc file in the ~git dir cannot not influence <span class="caps">PATH</span> before sshd runs the command in the authorized_keys file.</p>


	<p>A solution is to set <span class="caps">PATH</span> in ~git/.ssh/environment
&lt;&lt;&lt;
<span class="caps">PATH</span>=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/sbin:/usr/bin:/bin,
&lt;&lt;&lt;</p>


	<p>(If there is a more portable way to do this? I would appreciate someone pointing it out.  I tried
<span class="caps">PATH</span>=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:$PATH
and it did not work.)</p>


	<p>and set &#8220;PermitUserEnvironment yes&#8221; in /etc/ssh/sshd_config</p>
</div>
<div class="add-comment-line"><!-- add line here --></div>
</div>

