<span class="user-postname"><span>Cesar</span></span><span class="user-date"> on April 13, 2009 09:56 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>Regarding non-standard <span class="caps">SSH</span> ports. You might consider rewriting the url as follows:
<del>-</del>: git@myserver.com:1234:/foo/bar
<ins>+</ins>: ssh://git@myserver.com:1234/foo/bar</p>


	<p>and everything works like a charm without any need of changing ~/.ssh/config</p>
</div>
