<div class="user-text">
<p>These instructions worked fine on Ubuntu 9.0.4 with one minor bug: &#8220;python setup.py install&#8221; requires a sudo since it&#8217;s creating files in /usr/local/bin (among other places).</p>


	<p>The correct command should be: &#8220;sudo python setup.py install&#8221; (without quotes).</p>
