<p>as grempe wrote above already&#8212;see &#8220;grempe on November 19, 2007 02:37 PM&#8221;</p>


	<p>I set things up as told here
http://sunoano.name/ws/public_xhtml/scm.html#provide_a_git_repository_to_the_public</p>


	<p>then I also wanted to use &#8220;daemon = yes&#8221; so the file git-daemon-export-ok get&#8217;s autogenerated by gitosis and git-daemon knows it can serve this paritcular repo to anonymous users.</p>


<h2>Bottom Line:</h2>	<p>Setting daemon = yes in the [group foo] stanza in .gitosis.conf does not autogenerate ../foo.git/git-daemon-export-ok and thus foo.git cannot be served in read-only mode to anonymous users.</p>



	<p>How do we solve this issue resp. make it work as expected? Maybe some of us do something wrong? I am using the debian gitosis package.</p>
