<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><a href="http://tomster.org/">tomster</a></span><span class="user-date"> on September 06, 2009 11:02 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>I found a bit simpler way to install gitosis without &#8216;polluting&#8217; the system-wide python. To get it working with virtualenv all is necessary is to replace the two calls in the post-update hook with absolute paths. No mucking about with $PYTHONPATH (evil!!) or /etc/environment.</p>


	<p>You can find a more detailed write-up over at my blog, if you need: http://tomster.org/blog/archive/2009/09/06/gitosis-and-virtualenv</p>
</div>
<div class="add-comment-line"><!-- add line here --></div>
</div>

