<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><span>Manu</span></span><span class="user-date"> on September 22, 2009 05:50 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>Hi,</p>


	<p>thanks for the great post.</p>


	<p>As far as I can see, the gitosis operations on the server will run as &#8220;git&#8221; (with the user &#8220;git&#8221;). Is there a way to prevent users (who push code) from doing anything beyond pushing code ?</p>


	<p>If I am right (and I am probably not), the git user is just open to anybody (no password), and has a shell, so anybody can login the box as &#8220;git&#8221; and do whatever he wants.</p>


	<p>Where am I wrong ?</p>
