<!-- comments layout -->
<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><a href="http://www.lanttern.com">Alex</a></span><span class="user-date"> on October 14, 2009 10:15 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>I was experiencing the following error as well:</p>


	<p><span class="caps">ERROR</span>:gitosis.serve.main:Repository read access denied
fatal: The remote end hung up unexpectedly</p>


	<p>Upon inspecting .gitosis.conf in /home/git I discovered that it wasn&#8217;t being updated to reflect my <span class="caps">PUSH</span>.</p>


	<p>You <span class="caps">MUST</span> update permissions to 755 on the file /home/git/repositories/gitosis-admin.git/hooks/post-update , otherwise the configuration will not be updated.</p>


	<p>So do that, then modify gitosis.conf so that git picks up the change, commit, and <span class="caps">PUSH</span> again.</p>


	<p>This time everything should work!</p>
</div>
<div class="add-comment-line"><!-- add line here --></div>
