<span class="user-postname"><a href="http://www.dedoware.com">adouglas</a></span><span class="user-date"> on March 05, 2010 03:59 PM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>Great guide. Was having some trouble creating a new git repo, basically geting a</p>


	<p>fatal: &#8216;gitosis-admin.git&#8217;: unable to chdir or not a git archive
fatal: The remote end hung up unexpectedly</p>


	<pre><code>and reinstalled everything from scratch. I realized I had encountered the error before but had forgotten where it was coming from. I believe the latest version of gitosis creates a repositories folder, so the instructions are no longer accurate, since you need git clone git@youservername.com/home/git/repositories/gitosis-admin.git</code></pre>


	<p>Hope this helps!</p>
