<span class="user-postname"><span>Mahesh Vaidya</span></span><span class="user-date"> on March 10, 2010 02:22 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>Hi,</p>


	<p>I would like to version control all my server side hooks per repository basis. Basically I am (trying) to keep all my hooks / repository basis in git admin repos.</p>


	<p>Each time a push is done to gitosis-admin, I would like gitosis post-update trigger to copy those hooks to respective repository.</p>


	<p>Any such feature available ? or way to add extension in gitosis</p>


	<p>Thank You
-Mahesh Vaidya</p>
</div>
