<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><a href="http://devth.com">devth</a></span><span class="user-date"> on April 22, 2010 02:57 PM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>Setting this up on a different <span class="caps">OSX</span> box after a successful setup on another machine, I flew thru the tut and skipped the step:
sudo chmod 755 /home/git/repositories/gitosis-admin.git/hooks/post-update</p>


	<p>That was a fail because it turns out it wasn&#8217;t executable by default. Trying to add additional users wouldn&#8217;t work because of that, and I was receiving the dreaded &#8220;ERROR:gitosis.serve.main:Repository read access denied&#8221;.  Make sure to double check that it&#8217;s executable!</p>


	<p>@garry Excellent writeup. Thank you, sir.</p>
</div>
