<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><span>MoeJoe</span></span><span class="user-date"> on June 23, 2010 06:57 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>A warning for others. I am investigating Git to use at my company. I didn&#8217;t want to pollute our current <span class="caps">SCM</span> server, so I used my machine as both the client and server. Epic fail and frustration. Not certain if it is because of client and server on the same box, some configuration cruft from past investigations, or something else. If you are trying gitosis with the same setup and things are not working, give it up and find another machine to use as a server. Once I put the server on a different box, things went smooth.</p>


	<p>One note to make the discussion easier to follow. There are lots of gits floating around: git the <span class="caps">SCM</span> tool, git the user, git the party mix. It would be clearer if the git user was called something else, maybe gituser, user, ...</p>


	<p>Thanks for the excellent writeup.</p>
</div>
