<div id="comments-box"> 
<span class="user-postname"><span>Sean</span></span><span class="user-date"> on July 25, 2010 12:52 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>Just thought I&#8217;d mention to everyone that the failure &#8220;Permission denied ( publickey).&#8221; can be caused by an incorrect shell for the &#8216;git&#8217; user. You do mention</p>


	<p>I fat-fingered the &#8216;adduser&#8217; command, and the shell ended up being &#8221;/bin/sh/&#8221;. That extra slash at the end was causing some issues. Took a while to figure out ( had to edit /etc/passwd manually ), but once I had it figured out it was a quick fix. You do mention that &#8220;the user does not need a password, but does need a valid shell (otherwise, <span class="caps">SSH</span> will refuse to work)&#8221;, but the error message for getting the shell wrong is a bit misleading.</p>
</div>
<div class="add-comment-line"><!-- add line here --></div>
</div>

