<span class="user-postname"><a href="http://eivanov.com">eivanov</a></span><span class="user-date"> on August 18, 2010 10:21 AM</span>
<div class="user-text">
<p>I&#8217;ve fixed &#8220;sh: gitosis-serve: command not found&#8221; with modifying /home/git/.ssh/authorized_keys (gitosis-serve-&gt;/usr/local/bin/gitosis-serve for default <span class="caps">PATH</span>). It looks like ssh executes it before ~/.bashrc is read (for non-login non-interactive shells it&#8217;s the only thing which is read).</p>
</div>
